<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,260,287]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Recognition.</emphasis>
In the key to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[552,669,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,669,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males of the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[976,1122,261,287]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref21228" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 175 lead 
<specimenCount box="[151,203,297,323]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="generic">
2 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz. In" authorityName="Schmitz. In" authorityYear="1935" box="[172,203,298,323]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subfuscipes">
<emphasis box="[172,203,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
subfuscipes Schmitz. In a revision of this complex (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[790,936,297,323]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="211 - 225" refId="ref21370" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (2014) Revisionary notes on the Megaselia sulphuripes (Meigen) species group (Dipt., Phoridae). Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 150, 211 - 225." type="journal article" year="2014">Disney 2014</bibRefCitation>
) this was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brues)" authorityName="Brues" baseAuthorityName="Brues" baseAuthorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ledburiensis">
<emphasis box="[1262,1436,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. ledburiensis</emphasis>
(Brues)
</taxonomicName>
, a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wood)" authorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[535,805,333,360]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutissima">
<emphasis box="[535,710,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. minutissima</emphasis>
(Wood)
</taxonomicName>
whose name was preoccupied by a species from New 
<collectingCountry box="[151,236,369,395]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. In this revision it runs to couplet 178 lead 
<specimenCount box="[740,794,369,395]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="generic">
2 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wood)" authorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[763,794,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halterata">
<emphasis box="[763,794,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
halterata (Wood) on the basis of its pale haltere knobs. However, its costal cilia and outer axillary bristles are at least 
<quantity box="[860,961,405,431]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long, its left hypandrial lobe is upcurved, strongly tapered and devoid of microtrichia (
<figureCitation box="[656,836,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 201–204" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1570,1595]" captionTargetBox="[211,1383,604,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[197,1391,597,1545]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 201–204. Details of males of Megaselia species close to M. ledzona. 201–203, M. halterata details of hypopygium. 201, left face of hypopygium; 202, left face of hypandrium; 203, right face of hypandrium; 204, left face of abdomen of M. ledburiensis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573426/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 201 &amp; 202</figureCitation>
) and the right hypandrial lobe is absent (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1398,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 201–204" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1570,1595]" captionTargetBox="[211,1383,604,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[197,1391,597,1545]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 201–204. Details of males of Megaselia species close to M. ledzona. 201–203, M. halterata details of hypopygium. 201, left face of hypopygium; 202, left face of hypandrium; 203, right face of hypandrium; 204, left face of abdomen of M. ledburiensis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573426/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 203</figureCitation>
). If at couplet 178 one ignores the haltere knob being not yellow, but brown, one proceeds to couplet 180. Taking lead 1 one then proceeds to couplet 181 lead 
<specimenCount box="[615,668,513,539]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="generic">
1 
<taxonomicName box="[637,668,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ledburyensis">
<emphasis box="[637,668,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
ledburyensis, which is immediately distinguished by the fewer and smaller hairs on the abdominal venter (
<figureCitation box="[594,693,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 201–204" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1570,1595]" captionTargetBox="[211,1383,604,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[197,1391,597,1545]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 201–204. Details of males of Megaselia species close to M. ledzona. 201–203, M. halterata details of hypopygium. 201, left face of hypopygium; 202, left face of hypandrium; 203, right face of hypandrium; 204, left face of abdomen of M. ledburiensis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573426/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 204</figureCitation>
). Lead 2 of couplet 180 is the Canary Islands species 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apozona">
<emphasis box="[1303,1436,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. apozona</emphasis>
Schmitz
</taxonomicName>
, whose left hypandrial lobe is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[795,936,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halterata">
<emphasis box="[795,936,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. halterata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[993,1181,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName box="[993,1177,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ledburyensis">M. ledburyensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Otherwise the species fails to run down in the rest of the world literature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1199,657,683]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,152,683]" box="[199,1199,657,683]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,657,683]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after it being intermediate between 
<taxonomicName box="[826,1005,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ledburyensis">
<emphasis box="[826,1005,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">M. ledburyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1059,1199,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1936" box="[1059,1195,658,683]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apozona">M. apozona</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
